info.description: ATSPM Log Data with OpenAPI, Swashbuckle, and API versioning.

get.summary: Retrieves the available derived data types defined in the system.

parameters.name: X-Timestamp-Format
parameters.description: Change CSV timestamp format https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/standard/base-types/custom-date-and-time-format-strings

200.description: Call completed successfully and returns the list of data types.

500.description: An unexpected error occurred while retrieving data types.

get.summary: Streams archived data records for a specific location within a given date range.
get.description:
### Response Format
- Content type: `application/x-ndjson`
- Each line is a JSON object representing a <typeparamref name="T1" /> record.
- Clients should parse line-by-line rather than expecting a JSON array.
            
### Example Request
- GET /StreamData/1014?start=2024-01-01&end=2024-12-31
            
### Example Response (NDJSON)
```
{"locationId":"1014","start":"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z","end":"2024-01-01T23:59:59Z"}
{"locationId":"1014","start":"2024-01-02T00:00:00Z","end":"2024-01-02T23:59:59Z"}
```
            
### Streaming and Cancellation
- Results are streamed using `IAsyncEnumerable`.
- Clients can cancel by aborting the HTTP request (e.g., disposing `HttpClient` in .NET or calling `AbortController.abort()` in JavaScript).
- Cancellation immediately stops enumeration and closes the response.

parameters.name: locationIdentifier
parameters.description: Unique identifier of the location whose data are requested.

parameters.name: start
parameters.description: Inclusive start date of the archive range. Must be less than or equal to end.

parameters.name: end
parameters.description: Inclusive end date of the archive range. Must be greater than or equal to start.

parameters.name: X-Timestamp-Format
parameters.description: Change CSV timestamp format https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/standard/base-types/custom-date-and-time-format-strings

400.description: Invalid date range or malformed request.
